#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:48
msgid ""
"The branch server will bootstrap the terminals according to the data you "
"have provided."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "Re-Deploy Images to the Terminals"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:50
msgid ""
"You can instruct terminals to download and deploy images when they are "
"restarted.  This is achieved using a Salt state."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:51
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Forcing a Terminal to Re-Deploy Images"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:52
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:58
msgid ""
"On the {productname} Server, at the command prompt, as root, apply this Salt "
"state:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:53
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt $terminal_minion_id state.apply saltboot.force_redeploy\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:54
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:60
msgid "Restart the terminal to pick up the changes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:55
msgid ""
"If your terminal encounters a problem with the file system or the partition "
"table, you might need to remove the partition table and reformat the "
"terminal."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:56
msgid ""
"Re-partitioning a terminal removes all data stored on the terminal hard "
"disk, including any persistent partitions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:57
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Forcing a Terminal to Re-partition the Hard Disk"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:59
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt $terminal_minion_id state.apply saltboot.force_repartition\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "Customize the Terminal Image Download Process"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:62
msgid ""
"You can change the terminal boot process using Salt pillars.  Two Salt "
"pillars allow you to change the protocol and server used to download the "
"image."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:63
msgid ""
"The ``saltboot_download_protocol`` pillar specifies which protocol should be "
"used to download the image to the terminal.  This overrides the default "
"protocol specified in the image pillar.  Allowed values are ``http``, "
"``https``, ``ftp``, or ``tftp``."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:64
msgid ""
"The ``saltboot_download_server`` pillar specifies which server to use to "
"download the image.  This overrides the default hostname specified in the "
"image pillar."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:65
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example: Changing the Saltboot Image Download Protocol"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:66
msgid "This example changes the protocol used for all terminals."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:67
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:73
msgid "Edit the ``/srv/pillar/top.sls`` file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:68
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"base:\n"
"  '*':\n"
"    - saltboot_proto\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:69
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:75
msgid "Edit the ``/srv/pillar/$branch_prefix.sls`` file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:70
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"saltboot_download_protocol: http\n"
"# can be http, https, ftp, tftp\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:71
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example: Changing the Saltboot Image Download Location"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:72
msgid ""
"This example changes the download location for all terminals on a specified "
"branch server."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:74
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"base:\n"
"  'minion_id_prefix:$branch_prefix':\n"
"     - match: grain\n"
"     - $branch_prefix\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:76
#, no-wrap
msgid "saltboot_download_server: $download_server_fqdn\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-deploy-terminals.adoc:77
msgid ""
"In this example, the download server must be prepared by the ``image_sync`` "
"state before you begin."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-formulas-intro.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Introduction to Retail Formulas"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-formulas-intro.adoc:2
msgid ""
"Formulas are pre-written Salt states, that are used to configure your "
"{productname} {smr} installation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-formulas-intro.adoc:3
msgid ""
"You can use the {productname} {webui} to apply common {productname} "
"formulas.  For the most commonly used formulas, see xref:salt:formulas-intro."
"adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-formulas-intro.adoc:4
msgid ""
"All formulas must be accurately configured for your {productname} {smr} "
"installation to function correctly.  If you are unsure of the correct "
"formula configuration details, run the [command]``retail_branch_init`` "
"command before you begin to create the recommended formula configuration.  "
"You can then manually edit the formulas as required."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-formulas-intro.adoc:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "Branch Server Formulas"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-formulas-intro.adoc:6
msgid ""
"Branch servers are configured using formulas.  Formulas can be configured "
"using {productname} {webui}, or the {productname} XMLRPC API.  To fully "
"configure {productname} {smr}, these formulas need to be enabled and "
"configured on the branch server:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-formulas-intro.adoc:7
msgid "Branch network formula, see xref:salt:formula-branchnetwork.adoc[]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-formulas-intro.adoc:8
msgid "Bind formula, see xref:salt:formula-bind.adoc[]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-formulas-intro.adoc:9
msgid "DHCPD formula, see xref:salt:formula-dhcpd.adoc[]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-formulas-intro.adoc:10
msgid "PXE formula, see xref:salt:formula-pxe.adoc[]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-formulas-intro.adoc:11
msgid "TFTP formula, see xref:salt:formula-tftpd.adoc[]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-formulas-intro.adoc:12
msgid "VSFTP formula, see xref:salt:formula-vsftpd.adoc[]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-formulas-intro.adoc:13
msgid ""
"Optionally, you can also enable the image synchronization formula.  For more "
"information, see xref:salt:formula-imagesync.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-formulas-intro.adoc:14
msgid ""
"Badly configured formulas can result in the branch server failing to work as "
"expected.  Due to the generic nature of formulas it is difficult to do "
"overall validation.  We recommend that you configure the branch server using "
"the {productname} {smr} command line utilities, and use individual formula "
"settings for further tuning if required.  For more information, see xref:"
"retail:retail-install-setup.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-formulas-intro.adoc:15
msgid ""
"If a formula uses the same name as an existing Salt state, the two names "
"will collide.  This could result in the formula being used instead of the "
"state.  Always check the names of states and formulas to avoid name "
"collisions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-formulas-intro.adoc:16
msgid ""
"When you have made changes to your formula, ensure you apply the highstate.  "
"The highstate propagates your changes to the appropriate services."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-formulas-intro.adoc:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "Partitioning and Image Deployment Formula"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-formulas-intro.adoc:18
msgid ""
"Use the Saltboot formula to specify disk partitioning, and to select which "
"image should be deployed.  For more information about the Saltboot formula, "
"see xref:salt:formula-saltboot.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

