#. type: Title =
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-intro.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Retail Migration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-intro.adoc:2
msgid ""
"This section provides instructions for migrating {slepos} 11, {productname} "
"{smr} 3.1, or {productname} {smr} 3.2 to {productname} {smr} 4.1."
msgstr ""

#.  FIXME
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-intro.adoc:3
msgid ""
"For migrating {productname} {smr} to the latest version, see the "
"{productname} upgrade instructions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Migrate {slepos} 11 to {productname} {smr}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:2
msgid ""
"This section describes migrating from an existing {slepos} 11 installation "
"to a new {productname} installation.  You can perform this migration all at "
"once by creating a data dump in a single file, and then moving it to the new "
"server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:3
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can perform the migration in stages by creating a data "
"dump for each branch, and moving them to the new server one by one.  "
"Importing and deploying the converted data can also be done in one or "
"multiple steps, depending on your environment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "Migration with Complete Data Dump"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:5
msgid ""
"In this procedure, you create a single data dump in an XML file, convert it "
"to YAML, and migrate it to the new infrastructure all at once."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:6
msgid ""
"Install the {productname} {smr} server {productnumber}.  For more "
"information, see xref:retail:retail-install-unified.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:7
msgid ""
"On the SLEPOS Admin server export all the data stored in LDAP to an XML "
"file.  Run this command as an administrator:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:8
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "posAdmin --export --type xml --file dumpfile.xml\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:9
msgid ""
"The resulting [literal]``dumpfile.xml`` file will contain global "
"information, with parts about images, hardware and its partitioning, and the "
"description of the branch servers with networking data, services, and "
"attached terminals."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:10
msgid ""
"Move the XML file to the newly created {productname} server, and convert it "
"to YAML:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "retail_migration dumpfile.xml retail.yml\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:12
msgid ""
"Review the generated YAML file ([literal]``retail.yml``) and adjust it as "
"necessary.  Consider ``HWTYPE`` group naming and image name and version "
"changes in the partitioning data.  Group names must not exceed the "
"56 character limit.  You can shorten the names as needed, and the image "
"names must match the images in {productname}.  The [option]``--save-"
"mapping`` option can help you with this task."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:13
msgid ""
"Also check whether there are duplicate MAC addresses of the terminals in the "
"generated YAML file.  Choose which entry you want to keep.  If there are "
"duplicate MAC addresses, importing the YAML file will fail."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:14
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:31
msgid ""
"{slepos} images will not be migrated. You must rebuild the images using the "
"OS image building functionality.  For more information about building "
"images, see xref:administration:image-management.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:15
msgid "Import the complete data (YAML) with:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "retail_yaml --from-yaml retail.yml\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:17
msgid ""
"You can see statistical data while the import is in progress.  Check the "
"results in the {webui} by navigating to menu:Systems[System List > All] and "
"find empty profiles.  To see the groups for the hardware configuration, "
"branches, servers, and terminals, navigate to menu:Systems[Groups]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:18
msgid ""
"To finalize the branch server migration, you must install the branch server "
"machines as Salt clients and bootstrap them as proxies.  For more "
"information about proxy installation, see xref:retail:retail-install."
"adoc[].  For more information about using an activation key to assign the "
"required channels, see xref:retail:retail-install-setup.adoc[].  After "
"onboarded to {productname}, the branch servers machines are connected with "
"the empty profiles (by FQDN), and so they will get the Retail configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:19
msgid ""
"After all the branches are migrated, shutdown and remove the old SLEPOS "
"Admin Server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "Migration with Branch by Branch Data Dump"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:21
msgid ""
"In this procedure, you migrate the SLEPOS infrastructure and the branches "
"one by one, first exporting and then importing."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:22
msgid ""
"Install the {productname} {smr} server {productnumber} For more information, "
"see xref:retail:retail-install-unified.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:23
msgid "On every branch server:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:25
msgid ""
"These dumps will contain only the LDAP data of the branch, and any global "
"data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:26
msgid ""
"Similarily, you can export the LDAP data of every branch if you run the "
"command on the Admin server with the branch credentials explicitly specified:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:27
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"posAdmin --export --type xml --file dumpfile.xml --user $branch_dn \\\n"
"    --password $password\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:28
msgid ""
"For background information about SLEPOS branch server configuration, see "
"https://documentation.suse.com/sle-pos/11-SP3/html/SLEPOS-guide/cha."
"slepos_branchserv.html."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:29
msgid ""
"Review the generated YAML file ([literal]``retail.yml``) and adjust it as "
"necessary.  Consider ``HWTYPE`` group naming and image name and version "
"changes in the partitioning data.  You can shorten the names as needed, and "
"the image names must match the images in {productname}.  The [option]``--"
"save-mapping`` option can help you with this task."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:30
msgid ""
"Check whether there are duplicate MAC addresses of the terminals in the "
"generated YAML file.  Choose which entry you want to keep.  As long as there "
"are duplicate MAC addresses, {productname} will refuse importing the YAML "
"file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:32
msgid ""
"The data can be imported branch by branch.  For each branch perform the "
"following steps:"
msgstr ""

#.  . Replace each old SLEPOS branch server with the {productname} {smr} branch server (see https://www.suse.com/documentation/suse-manager-for-retail-3-2/retail-getting-started/retail.chap.install.html[Install Branch Server]) and connect it to the {productname} {smr} server (the same procedure as for https://www.suse.com/documentation/suse-manager-for-retail-3-2/retail-getting-started/retail.chap.admin.html#retail.sect.admin.branch_mass_config[Branch Server Mass Configuration]).
#.  +
#.  Use the empty profiles together with activation keys to onboard all the systems of your infrastructure.
#.  Use an activation key to assign the channels listed in https://www.suse.com/documentation/suse-manager-for-retail-3-2/retail-getting-started/retail.chap.install.html[Configuring Server].
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:33
msgid "Run the import command for one branch after the other:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:34
#, no-wrap
msgid "retail_yaml --from-yaml retail.yml --branch <branch_name>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:35
msgid "Repeat the command for every branch."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:36
msgid ""
"To finalize each branch server migration, you must install the branch server "
"machine as a Salt-based client and bootstrap it as a proxy.  For more "
"information about proxy installation, see xref:retail-install.adoc#retail."
"sect.install.branch[Installing and Registering].  For more information about "
"using an activation key to assign the required channels, see xref:retail-"
"install.adoc#retail.sect.install.install.config[Configuring Server].  After "
"onboarded to {productname} {smr}, the branch server machine is connected "
"with the empty profile (by FQDN), and so it will get the Retail "
"configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:37
msgid ""
"Apply Highstate on the branch server; this will happen automatically if "
"[guimenu]``Configuration File Deployment`` is enabled."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:38
msgid "Boot the terminals of the branch."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:39
msgid ""
"After all the branches are migrated, shut down and remove the old SLEPOS "
"Admin Server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "Converting XML to YAML"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:41
msgid ""
"When you perform a migration using one of the methods in this chapter, one "
"of the steps takes the XML data dump file from {slepos}, and converts it to "
"a YAML file for {productname} {smr}.  The tool that performs this conversion "
"has additional features, which are outlined in this section."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:42
msgid "To validate the XML file before conversion, and print any errors:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:43
#, no-wrap
msgid "retail_migration dumpfile.xml\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:44
msgid "To write a mapping file called [path]``map.yml``:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "retail_migration dumpfile.xml  --save-mapping map.yml\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:46
msgid "The mapping file contains two dictionaries:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:47
msgid ""
"[systemitem]``images``, which maps old {slepos} images to new images built "
"in {productname}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:48
msgid ""
"[systemitem]``groups``, which maps legacy {slepos} "
"[systemitem]``scCashRegister`` objects to {productname} "
"[systemitem]``HWTYPE`` groups.  Group names must not exceed the 56 character "
"limit."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:49
msgid "The mapping file should be edited as required for your environment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:50
msgid "To perform a conversion using a mapping file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:51
#, no-wrap
msgid "retail_migration dumpfile.xml  retail.yml --mapping map.yml\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:52
msgid ""
"If you are performing a branch-by-branch migration, the resulting "
"[path]``retail.yml`` file will contain a new version of {slepos} LDAP data.  "
"If you want to preserve any global changes in your {productname} {smr} "
"settings, remove the [systemitem]``global`` hardware types from the "
"resulting [path]``retail.yml`` file before importing it.  Alternatively, you "
"can import [path]``retail.yml`` using this command to import only the new "
"systems and groups defined in the file, and leave any existing configuration "
"settings untouched:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-migration-slepostosuma.adoc:53
#, no-wrap
msgid "retail_yaml --only-new\n"
msgstr ""

#
#. type: Title =
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Network Architecture"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:2
msgid "{productname} {smr} uses a layered architecture:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:3
msgid "The first layer contains the {productname} Server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:4
msgid ""
"The second layer contains one or more branch servers to provide local "
"network and boot services."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:5
msgid "It also contains one or more build hosts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:6
msgid ""
"The final layer contains any number of deployed point-of-service terminals."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "retail_arch.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-network-arch.adoc:8
msgid ""
"Branch servers should be physically located close to point-of-service "
"terminals, such as in an individual store or branch office.  We recommend "
"you have a fast network connection between the branch server and its "
